---
import SectionLayout from "../layouts/section-layout.astro";
---

<SectionLayout title="Film Submission" id="submission">
  <Fragment slot="content">
    <!-- Submission Content -->
    <div class="submission-content">
      <div class="submissions-closed-banner">
        <h2>Submissions Currently Closed</h2>
        <p class="submissions-notice">Submissions for the 2026 festival have ended. Submissions for 2027 will open in June 2026!</p>
      </div>
      <div class="mb-8 flex justify-center">
        <div class="disabled-button" title="Submission period has passed">
          <img src="https://public-assets.filmfreeway.com/submission_buttons/v2/med_submission_btn@2x-sky-gradient.png" alt="Submissions closed" width="263" height="102">
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="subheader-orange">Submission Guidelines:</h2>
      <div class="text-left">
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-4 mb-8">
          <li><strong>Genre:</strong> Films must be primarily comedy.</li>
          <li><strong>Completion Date:</strong> Films should have been completed after January 1, 2025.</li>
          <li><strong>Language:</strong> Non-English films must include English subtitles.</li>
          <li><strong>Length:</strong> Films should not exceed 20 minutes.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <h2 class="subheader-orange">Key Dates:</h2>
      <div class="text-left">
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-4 mb-8">
          <li><strong>Submissions Open:</strong> June 1, 2026</li>
          <li><strong>Submission Deadline:</strong> December 31, 2026</li>
          <li><strong>Notification Date:</strong> January 14, 2027</li>
          <li><strong>Festival Date:</strong> March 2027 (Day TBD)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h2 class="subheader-orange">AI & Synthetic Media Policy (2027)</h2>
      <div class="ai-policy-section">
        <p class="policy-intro">
          The Cookies & Comedy Film Festival recognizes that AI tools are increasingly part of modern filmmaking workflows. Rather than attempting to regulate every possible use, the festival is making a focused, pragmatic choice about character and performance.
        </p>

        <div class="policy-restrictions">
          <h4 class="policy-subheader">The following are not permitted:</h4>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-3">
            <li><strong>AI-generated characters</strong>, including foreground or background characters. This includes AI-generated faces, bodies, voices, or performances intended to function as characters in the film.</li>
            <li><strong>Synthetic replicas of real people</strong> (voice or likeness) without explicit consent from the individual depicted (and legal guardians where applicable).</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <p class="policy-purpose">
          This policy prioritizes human performance and authorship, and is intentionally aligned with evolving labor protections for performers and creators.
        </p>

        <div class="policy-notes">
          <p><strong>Note:</strong> Filmmakers will be asked to disclose AI use during submission.</p>
          <p class="policy-disclaimer">As labor organizations such as SAG-AFTRA establish clearer standards, consent models, and compensation frameworks for AI-generated character usage, the festival will revisit this policy accordingly.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Fragment>
</SectionLayout>

<style>
  /* .subheader-orange now handled globally */

  /* Banner Styling */
  .submissions-closed-banner {
    background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
    color: var(--color-secondary);
    text-align: center;
    padding: 1.5rem 1.5rem 2rem 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
    border: 1px solid rgba(215, 155, 88, 0.1);
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .submissions-closed-banner h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--color-secondary);
    text-shadow: none;
  }
  
  .submissions-notice {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  /* Submission Content */
  .submission-content {
    /* No special styling needed when enabled */
  }

  /* Disabled button styling */
  .disabled-button {
    opacity: 0.4;
    filter: grayscale(100%);
    cursor: not-allowed;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  /* Remove the previous submission-closed-tag */
  .submissions-closed-tag {
    display: none;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    /* No special styles needed */
  }

  /* AI Policy Section */
  .ai-policy-section {
    background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
    padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-secondary);
    text-align: left;
  }

  .policy-intro {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .policy-restrictions {
    background-color: rgba(215, 155, 88, 0.1);
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .policy-subheader {
    font-family: 'Nunito Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .policy-purpose {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .policy-notes {
    padding-top: 1rem;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(215, 155, 88, 0.3);
  }

  .policy-notes p {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .policy-disclaimer {
    color: var(--color-text-light);
    font-style: italic;
  }
</style>
